bio.experienceSummary:
As a caregiver, my passion is to nurture and support children's growth and development. With four years of experience caring for children of all ages, I have honed my skills in creating a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment where children can thrive. I'm patient, calm, and empathetic, and I believe in open communication with parents to ensure the best care for their children.

My approach to childcare focuses on creative play, outdoor activities, and educational games that foster learning and imagination. I'm happy to help with cooking, light housekeeping, travel, and supervising swimming. I hold First Aid and CPR certifications and have completed coursework in early child development.

I'm excited about the opportunity to bring my skills and experience to your family and provide your child with the care and attention they deserve. Together, we can create a positive and nurturing environment where your child can flourish and reach their full potential.

Hi! My name is Marisa and I am 29 years old, currently residing in union county, NJ. I am a social worker, currently working as a case manager and crisis counselor at a higher education institution. Due to the nature of academics, I am looking for part-time summer work. I have had over 15 years of experience working with children of all ages (0-18), I love pets, and have my own car if transportation is needed!

I would describe myself as outgoing, compassionate and responsible.


 I find child care to be very fulfilling. It's a joy to watch them grow and meet new milestones. I grew up in a large family with lots of children and find child care to come naturally to me.

I'm looking for a job that harbors a positive environment and gives me the opportunity to help families while working towards my psychology degree.

 I have experience with children of nearly all ages, including infants, toddlers, elementary and middle schoolers.

 I love doing anything creative, baking, sculpting, crafting, you name it.

Although I strive to keep a fun and light atmosphere, I pride myself on being prepared for anything, even the worst case scenarios. I am quick to act in an emergency and I take safety seriously.

My skills include maintaining and monitoring safety, preparing balanced meals, and assisting with learning and development. I am willing to help with housekeeping and pet care if needed.

description.displayText: Natalie has a calming demeanor and is very honest and straightforward. She was sweet to our 1.5 year old son and was able to keep him engaged throughout. She followed our instructions well and her previous experience with children was clear through the way she handled herself. I would hire Natalie again and we recommend her.

bio.experienceSummary: My name is Christine and I have been watching kids since I was 16. I like go to the park and play games with the kids. Love watching them enjoy themselves. I cooked, bathed, did laundry for the kids as long parents were okay with it. Working with kids have been something I wanted to do since I was little. I have been working at a hospital since 2017 as a tech. I am in school as a social service major. I am certified in First Aid and CPR.

I am fun, caring and compassionate! Graduated from the University of Vermont in May of 2020 with a Dual Endorsement in Early Childhood Education and Special Education. I am First Aid and CPR certified as of June 2024. I have 13 years of experience with child care in various settings. 

I have a passion for children and enjoy playing, creating and exploring with our next generation! I am happy to answer any questions you may have and I look forward to meeting your little one(s). 

I do not smoke.

description.displayText: Allyson was wonderfully engaging, warm, and energetic with my two active children, ages 2.5 and 6.5. She is great with kids, and mine really loved spending the day with her. She communicated well with both me and them, and she found ways to keep them happy and busy. When my toddler son was feeling anxious about separating from me, Allyson was able to calm him down, which is not an easy feat. I really appreciated her being really attentive and responsible with the kids.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm a nurturing and enthusiastic childcare provider with a deep passion for nurturing children's growth and development. With 5 years of experience, I've had the privilege of caring for children from diverse backgrounds, helping them flourish in a safe and nurturing environment. My patient and calm demeanor, coupled with my creativity and imagination, allows me to engage children in educational and enjoyable activities that foster their learning and development.

I prioritize open communication with parents, providing written daily reports, verbal updates at pickup, and regular text or phone call updates. Ensuring the safety and well-being of children is paramount, which is why I'm very comfortable enforcing household rules.

I'm fluent in both English and Spanish, and I'm happy to help with light housekeeping tasks. I've completed First Aid Training and CPR Training, ensuring I'm well-equipped to handle any emergencies.

I am 31 with an undergraduate degree. I am the oldest of four children and was always taking care of my younger brothers, while my parents had to work. I have worked for several wonderful families over the past 11 years with children ranging in ages between 4 and 17. I enjoy playing with and watching younger children and also engaging with and guiding teens. Homework help, tutoring and studying come natural and I have no issue helping any age as I have tutoring experience. Lastly, I have a responsible, fun loving, upbeat, reliable and cheerful personality.

description.displayText: I have two daughters, my youngest has Autism. Sam is always on time, has excellent communication skills (always able to reach her), her own vehicle, has no issue staying late, and is wonderful with both my daughters. She is an absolute pleasure and am so pleased and grateful I was able to find her! Her personality, charm, energy, and attention to detail are some of the reasons I chose to hire her in the first place. She still works with us and when she's completed college and graduate school we will be sad to see her go.

bio.experienceSummary: I've always had a passion for helping children grow and develop, which is why I became a childcare provider. I want to have a positive impact on their lives and help support families by providing reliable childcare. I'm patient, creative, and friendly, and I love playing games with children, from outdoor sports to board games and educational games. With more than 20 years of experience caring for children and my Early Childhood Education degree, I'm well-equipped to provide a safe and nurturing environment for your child. I'm certified in First Aid and CPR, and I've taken coursework in Early Child Development. I'm happy to help with cooking, meal preparation, and light housekeeping and my house can be flexible on Monday, Tuesday and Thursday. I hope to have the opportunity to care for your child/children and help them learn and grow!

description.originalText: Grace is a caring, reliable babysitter who truly loves children. She connects with them effortlessly, keeps them engaged with fun activities, and ensures they feel valued. Her warmth and dedication make her a joy to have, and I highly recommend her to any family.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi Everyone ! I've been baby sitting my family and friends kids starting from a young age, so this is something I'm great at , I have patience , compassion and good communication skills to ensure a positive experience for both the children and their parents. I would be entrusted with the important task of caring for a child's well-being, which requires attention to detail and the ability to stay calm under pressure. I'm very big on cleaning houses, keeping everything neat and organized for when everyone comes home , I like to adventure around and interact with the little ones, I love to paint and draw , being outdoors it's something I enjoy , I'm also a 4th year college student criminal justice major doing this as a little side job until I go back to school , I'm also a hostess Friday through Sunday , I can also speak Spanish (Uruguayan ) overall, if you're interested, we can chat if my hours do not work with you and we can make an arrangement ! Thank you

description.originalText: Mia has supported our family for a year and a half.  Our twins adore her and have always been well taken care of.  She devotes her full attention to our children and interacts well with them during their studies, arts and crafts and other creative activities.  She’s been like family and we’ve  had full trust in her in childcare capabilities.

bio.experienceSummary: I'm the eldest of five. I have an infant of my own I need to be able to bring along at all times. I grew up helping take care of children all my life, both in   and outside babysitting jobs. A few years ago I also taught gymnastics to kids of all ages. My favorite activities to engage in with kids are arts and crafts and outside activities. I also have experience taking care of pets. I follow directions well and I help when and where I am needed. I am knowledgeable in many different areas and am capable of providing multiple services. I am available for pet sitting (at your location), house sitting, and babysitting. I have my own vehicle and I don't mind running errands or running your kids around. I am reliable, trustworthy and cheerful, and I have always had positive feedback from employers.

description.displayText:
Jessica is a wonderful babysitter! She is always willing to do any activity my toddler wants to do (even jumping in muddy puddles)! She is kind, patient and very well mannered. My two and half year old loves her. She also comes with fun art activities to do. 

Jessica is on time and is always easy to get in touch with. 

We are very happy with Jessica and hope to have her as a babysitter for a very long time!
